<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
With the provided macro definitions LFS_UNLOCK(cfg) expands to ((void)cfg), i.e. a no-op with no side-effects. The statement LFS_UNLOCK(lfs->cfg); is therefore executed but its removal would not affect program behaviour in this build, so it is dead code. (If LFS_UNLOCK is replaced in other configurations with an actual unlock operation, then it would not be dead; but as given it violates Rule 2.2.)
</scenario>
